---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import "@fontsource/jost/500.css";
import primary_colors from "../assets/images/primary_colors_thrifty.png";
import favicon from "../assets/images/favicon.png";
import logo from "../assets/images/logo.png";

import EvelinFilePainPoint from "./EvelinFilePainPoint.astro";
import EvelinFileWrapper from "./EvelinFileWrapper.astro";
import ReactImageWrapper from "./ReactImageWrapper";
import ShadyNumber from "./ShadyNumber.astro";
import thriftstudioKeyFeatures from "../thriftstudioKeyFeatures.ts";
import EvelinFileResearchGoal from "./EvelinFileResearchGoal.astro";
import ExpandDetails from "./ExpandDetails.astro";
import { adminInterface } from "../projects/evelinThriftstudioData";
import DynamicImgSrc from "./DynamicImgSrc";

const { fileTitle, bgColor, cardBgColor, id } = Astro.props;
---

<EvelinFileWrapper
  title={fileTitle}
  bgColor={bgColor}
  cardBgColor={cardBgColor}
  id={id}
  paddingX="px-[20px] sm:px-[50px] xl:px-[0px] 2xl:px-[172px]"
  paddingY="py-[80px] sm:py-[90px] xl:py-[130px]"
>
  <h3
    class="text-[21px] sm:text-[26px] sm:text-[26px] xl:text-[40px] text-[#1e1e1e] font-extrabold text-center"
  >
    WIREFRAMES
  </h3>

  <p
    class="mt-[20px] mx-[-20px] p-[20px] border-[#C8C9AC] border-t-[1px] border-b-[1px] text-[#1E1E1E] leading-[23px] sm:border-0 sm:mx-0 sm:rounded-[15px] sm:bg-[#E8E9C4] xl:rounded-[20px]"
  >
    I adopted a <strong>mobile-first approach</strong> in the initial sketching phase
    to ensure an intuitive user experience starting with the smallest screens. By
    focusing on mobile first, I was able to <strong
      >prioritize essential content</strong
    > and <strong>simplify interactions</strong>, ensuring that users would have
    an efficient experience even in constrained environments.
  </p>

  <div
    class="xl:flex xl:flex-row-reverse xl:justify-between xl:items-center xl:gap-[70px] xl:px-[78px] sm:mx-auto"
  >
    <ReactImageWrapper
      invertIcon={true}
      client:only
      imgClassName="rounded-[5px] w-[297px] mx-auto"
      className="mt-[30px] xl:mt-[40px]"
      src="thriftstudio_paper_wireframe"
    />

    <div class="">
      <p class="mt-[40px] sm:mt-[30px] mx-auto leading-[18px] text-[16px]">
        <strong>I started with laying out the key features:</strong>
      </p>

      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-[13px] xl:gap-[7px] mt-[23px] sm:mt-[20px] xl:mt-[30px]"
      >
        {
          thriftstudioKeyFeatures.map((item, i) => {
            return (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-[10px] xl:gap-[15px] text-[16px] xl:text-[17px]">
                <ShadyNumber>{i + 1}</ShadyNumber>
                <p class="leading-[17px]">{item.text}</p>
              </div>
            );
          })
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p
    class="bg-[#EDEAF6] p-[20px] sm:p-[24px] sm:rounded-[15px] mx-[-20px] sm:mx-0 mt-[25px] sm:mt-[50px] xl:mt-[40px]"
  >
    After finalizing the initial sketches, I transitioned to <strong
      >digital wireframes</strong
    >, prioritizing the key features. I designed both the primary and
    supplementary pages to establish a comprehensive user flow, ensuring the
    design was ready for user testing. I focused on <strong
      >three primary user tasks</strong
    > to evaluate the effectiveness of key interactions:
  </p>

  <ReactImageWrapper
    invertIcon={true}
    client:only
    className="mt-[25px] sm:mt-[30px] xl:mt-[40px]"
    src="thriftstudio_prototype"
  />

  <h4
    class="text-[17px] sm:text-[21px] xl:text-[32px] mt-[50px] xl:mt-[80px] font-bold"
  >
    USABILITY TESTING
  </h4>

  <section
    class="xl:grid xl:grid-cols-[1fr_286px] xl:gap-[94px] xl:items-center"
  >
    <div>
      <h5 class="text-[16px] font-bold mt-[20px] sm:mt-[40px] xl:text-[18px]">
        Goals:
      </h5>
      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-[3px] xl:gap-[12px]">
        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="sm:leading-[14px] xl:tracking-[0.5px] mt-[10px] w-fit"
          >assess whether users can successfully complete key tasks within the
          prototype</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >

        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="xl:tracking-[0.5px] sm:leading-[14px] w-fit"
        >
          evaluate the intuitiveness and usability of the prototype</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >
      </ul>

      <h5 class="text-[16px] font-bold mt-[30px] mt-[40px] xl:text-[18px]">
        Research questions:
      </h5>

      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-[3px] xl:gap-[12px] mt-[10px]">
        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="xl:tracking-[0.5px] sm:leading-[14px] w-fit"
          >what can we learn from the steps that users take to complete each
          task?</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >

        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="xl:tracking-[0.5px] sm:leading-[14px] w-fit"
          >are there parts of the user flow where users get stuck?</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >
        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="xl:tracking-[0.5px] sm:leading-[14px] w-fit"
          >do the users find the filter saving feature helpful and/or useful?</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >
        <EvelinFileResearchGoal
          bgColor="bg-[#EDEAF6]"
          padding="p-[12px]"
          textSize="text-[16px] xl:text-[16px]"
          className="xl:tracking-[0.5px] sm:leading-[14px] w-fit"
          >are there design changes that would make each task easier and/or
          faster for the users?</EvelinFileResearchGoal
        >
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h5
        class="text-[16px] font-bold sm:ml-[3px] text-center sm:text-left mt-[30px]"
      >
        Tasks
      </h5>
      <ol
        class="flex flex-col gap-[12px] list-decimal list-outside w-[100%] mx-auto pl-[20px] mt-[20px] font-medium leading-[18px]"
      >
        <li>Access your account and add a new shipping address</li>
        <li>Create and save a filter for "Brown sweaters in size 38"</li>
        <li>
          Used the saved filter to find a product, add it to your cart, and
          complete the purchase
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <h4
    class="text-[15px] sm:text-[17px] uppercase xl:normal-case text-center font-bold mt-[50px] xl:text-left"
  >
    Usability test findings<span class="hidden xl:inline">:</span>
  </h4>

  <div
    class="h-[1px] mx-[-20px] sm:mx-[-50px] w-screen mt-[15px] sm:hidden"
    style={{ backgroundColor: bgColor }}
  >
  </div>

  <div
    class="flex flex-col gap-[13px] sm:gap-[20px] xl:gap-[5px] mt-[15px] sm:mt-[20px] sm:border-[1px] sm:border-[#E8E9C4] sm:rounded-[15px] sm:py-[10px]"
  >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal
      noBg={true}
      className=""
      padding="px-4 pt-4"
      textSize="text-[16px]"
      >Participants found the Account menu overwhelming due to the numerous
      subsections and the need to navigate back and forth</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal noBg={true} padding="px-4" textSize="text-[16px]"
      >The radio button in the saved address section caused confusion, as its
      purpose (indicating the default address) was unclear</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal noBg={true} padding="px-4" textSize="text-[16px]"
      >Participants disliked that each filter section opened on a new page
      slowing the process, and found the “Type” list confusing, as it mixed
      product categories with options like “New in” and “Sale”</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal noBg={true} padding="px-4" textSize="text-[16px]"
      >Participants suggested adding color names to the color selection for
      better clarity</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal noBg={true} padding="px-4" textSize="text-[16px]"
      >While the filter saving feature was appreciated, accessing it was
      considered too cumbersome</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
    <EvelinFileResearchGoal
      noBg={true}
      padding="px-4 pb-4"
      textSize="text-[16px]"
      >Participants completed the checkout process smoothly but expressed a
      desire to see the cart total on every checkout page</EvelinFileResearchGoal
    >
  </div>

  <h3
    class="text-center text-[17px] sm:text-[21px] xl:text-[24px] font-bold mt-[40px] sm:mt-[95px]"
  >
    CHANGES
  </h3>

  <ExpandDetails
    bgColor={bgColor}
    iconId="thriftstudio_usability_test_icon"
    slotId="thriftstudio_usability_test_slot"
    buttonId="thriftstudio_usability_test_button"
    className="mt-[20px] sm:mt-[30px]"
  >
    <section class="xl:grid xl:grid-cols-2 xl:gap-[75px]">
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-[16px] mt-[30px] xl:mt-0">
          To address user frustrations with the account menu:
        </h4>

        <EvelinFilePainPoint
          bgColor={bgColor}
          className="mt-[20px] sm:mt-[30px]"
          textSize="text-[16px]"
          >I redesigned the navigation layout, replacing the vertical scrolling
          menu with horizontal scrolling, allowing users to access any section
          of their account with fewer clicks</EvelinFilePainPoint
        >
        <EvelinFilePainPoint
          bgColor={bgColor}
          className="mt-[15px] sm:mt-[20px]"
          textSize="text-[16px]"
          >The saved address card was revamped by replacing the confusing radio
          button and hidden menu with clearly visible editing options, enabling
          users to edit, delete, or set a default address with a single click</EvelinFilePainPoint
        >

        <EvelinFilePainPoint
          bgColor={bgColor}
          className="mt-[15px] sm:mt-[20px]"
          textSize="text-[16px]"
          >The default address is now visually highlighted for added clarity</EvelinFilePainPoint
        >
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-[16px] mt-[40px] xl:mt-0">
          To improve the filters section:
        </h4>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-[15px] mt-[20px] sm:mt-[30px]">
          <EvelinFilePainPoint bgColor={bgColor} textSize="text-[16px]"
            >I reorganized and divided filter categories to better align with
            their content, making it easier for users to locate and customize
            filters according to their preferences</EvelinFilePainPoint
          >
          <EvelinFilePainPoint bgColor={bgColor} textSize="text-[16px]"
            >Each filter category now uses a dropdown list instead of separate
            pages, with added icons for quick open/close actions, along with
            "Collapse All" and "Clear All" buttons for seamless navigation</EvelinFilePainPoint
          >
          <EvelinFilePainPoint bgColor={bgColor} textSize="text-[16px]"
            >I included color names to enhance clarity in the color filter</EvelinFilePainPoint
          >
          <EvelinFilePainPoint bgColor={bgColor} textSize="text-[16px]"
            >To improve access to saved filters, I separated them from the
            filtering page, introduced a dedicated button on the product page,
            and integrated them into the search function</EvelinFilePainPoint
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </ExpandDetails>

  <ReactImageWrapper
    invertIcon={true}
    client:only
    className="mt-[26px] sm:mt-[80px]"
    src="thriftstudio_before_after"
  />

  <h4
    class="text-right text-[17px] sm:text-[21px] xl:text-[24px] font-bold mt-[70px]"
  >
    ADMIN INTERFACE
  </h4>

  <p
    class="bg-[#EDEAF6] p-[20px] mx-[-20px] mt-[20px] sm:rounded-[15px] xl:rounded-[20px] xl:text-[17px]"
  >
    The admin interface was <strong
      >designed specifically for desktop use</strong
    > to provide ample space for <strong
      >overseeing large amounts of information</strong
    > and efficiently
    <strong>managing bulk product updates</strong>. I developed a <strong
      >mid-fidelity prototype</strong
    > to incorporate more detailed interactions, ensuring <strong
      >ease of use</strong
    > while accommodating <strong>various inventory management scenarios</strong
    >, such as editing, adding, and deleting products.
  </p>

  <DynamicImgSrc
    showByDefault={0}
    items={adminInterface}
    cardBgColor={cardBgColor}
    isAdminInterface={true}
    client:only
  />

  <h3 class="font-extrabold text-[21px] text-center mt-[80px]">
    STYLE DEFINITION
  </h3>
  <h4 class="text-[17px] font-bold text-left mt-[40px]">COLOR PALETTE</h4>

  <p class="text-[16px] mt-[20px]">
    To establish an <strong>energetic and fresh vibe</strong>, I chose a <strong
      >bright, vivid</strong
    > lime yellow as the primary color. Its vibrancy is balanced with two neutrals:
    an off-white for a <strong>light, airy feel</strong> and an almost-black for
    a subtle contrast, creating a <strong
      >minimalistic and modern aesthetic</strong
    >. To complement this foundation, I incorporated a range of grays, greens,
    and yellows, forming a cohesive and dynamic color palette that reinforces a <strong
      >strong and consistent visual identity</strong
    >.
  </p>

  <Image
    src={primary_colors}
    alt="the primary colors (white, mustard and black) of the thriftstudio app"
    class="mt-[20px]"
  />

  <ReactImageWrapper
    invertIcon={true}
    src="color_palette_thrifty"
    className="mt-[20px]"
    client:only
  />

  <h4 class="text-[17px] font-bold text-right mt-[50px]">TYPOGRAPHY</h4>
  <p class="mt-[20px] text-[16px]">
    To reflect the thrift store's diverse offerings, I aimed for a <strong
      >bold, expressive UI</strong
    >. I began with the logo, choosing the <strong
      >sans-serif font Staatliches</strong
    > for its <strong>dynamic and modern</strong> vibe. To make it stand out, I modified
    the first and last letters (T and O) and the repeating T's by cutting through
    them, creating an empty strike-through effect for a <strong
      >distinctive and edgy look</strong
    >.
  </p>

  <h4 class="font-bold text-[15px] text-center mt-[40px]">LOGO</h4>
  <Image
    src={logo}
    alt="thriftstudio logo variations in the three primary colors"
    class="mt-[10px]"
  />
  <h4 class="font-bold text-[15px] text-center mt-[20px]">FAVICON</h4>
  <div class="mx-auto">
    <Image
      src={favicon}
      alt="thriftstudio favicon, a black capital T with mustard background"
      class="block mx-auto mt-[10px]"
      width={50}
      height={50}
    />
  </div>

  <p class="text-[16px] mt-[40px]">
    As the <strong>primary font</strong> I have chosen <strong
      >Albert Sans</strong
    >, due to its modern aesthetic, legibility and extensive range of weights
    and styles, providing flexibility.
  </p>

  <p class="text-[16px] mt-[40px]">
    To draw attention to specific sections of the landing page, I incorporated a <strong
      >selection of sleek and distinctive typefaces</strong
    >, including Alokary, Allenoire, ITC Avant Garde Gothic, and Futura. Each
    font was chosen intentionally <strong
      >to add character and enhance the visual hierarchy</strong
    >, ensuring key elements stand out while maintaining a cohesive and modern
    aesthetic.
  </p>

  <ReactImageWrapper
    invertIcon={true}
    src="as_fonts"
    className="mt-[40px]"
    client:only
  />

  <ReactImageWrapper
    invertIcon={true}
    src="display_fonts"
    className="mt-[30px]"
    client:only
  />
</EvelinFileWrapper>
